{{wikipedia}}
==English==

===Etymology===
From wave (v.)

===Pronunciation===
*wāv, /weɪv/, /<tt>weIv</tt>/
*:'''Homophones''': [[waive]]
*:[[Rhymes:English:-eɪv|Rhymes: -eɪv]]

===Noun===
[[Category:English nouns]]
'''wave''' (''plural:'' '''[[waves]]''')
# A [[moving]] [[disturbance]] in the level of a body of [[water]].
#: ''The '''wave''' traveled from the center of the lake before breaking on the shore.''
# {{physics}} A moving disturbance in the [[energy]] [[level]] of a [[field]].
#: ''Gravity '''waves''', while [[predicted]] by [[theory]] for decades, have been notoriously difficult to detect.''
# A shape which alternately curves in opposite directions.
#: ''Her hair had a nice '''wave''' to it.''
# A suddenly unusually large amount of something that is temporarily experienced.
#:''A '''wave''' of shoppers [[stampede]]d through the door when the store opened for its Christmas discount special.''
#:''A '''wave''' of retirees began moving to the coastal area.''
#:''A '''wave''' of emotion overcame her when she thought about her son who was killed in battle.''
#A sideway movement of the hand(s).
#:''With a '''wave''' of the hand.''

