===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|wav|e}}

====Etymology====
{{OE.}} ''wafian'' "to wave with the hands", from Proto-Germanic ''*wab-'', from Proto-Indo-European base ''*webh-'' "to move to and fro, to weave"

====Intransitive====
[[Category:English intransitive verbs]]
# To move [[back]] and [[forth]] [[repeatedly]].
#: ''The flag '''waved''' in the gentle breeze.''
# To wave ones [[hand]] in greeting or departure.
#: ''I '''waved''' goodbye from across the room.''
#To have an [[undulating]] or [[wavy]] form.
# {{baseball}} To swing and miss at a pitch
#: ''Jones '''waves''' at strike one.''

